= Social Welfare Policy

The social welfare program, including unemployment insurance, healthcare, and old-age care, is the proudest achievement of the SPD. There is continuous pressure to dismantle the welfare system[? if black_thursday_seen = 1 :, especially given the economic crisis ?].

- @reduce_spending: Reduce spending on welfare.
- @increase_spending_pre_depression: Increase spending on welfare.
- @increase_spending_post_depression: Increase spending (welfare levels will remain about the same).
- @spending_same_pre_depression: Keep spending the same.
- @spending_same_post_depression: Keep spending the same (effectively a service cut).
- @easy_discard
#- @cancel_advisor_action

@reduce_spending
subtitle: This will hurt the workers. +1 Budget
unavailable-subtitle: There is nothing left to cut.
choose-if: welfare >= -5
on-arrival: budget += 1; workers_z -= 4; unemployed_z -= 4; catholic_z -= 2; workers_kpd += 1; workers_nsdap += 1; welfare -= 1; right_labor_dissent += 10; left_labor_dissent += 10; right_dissent -= 10; dvp_relation += 6; dnvp_relation += 6; spd_relation -= 5; pro_republic -= 3; coalition_dissent -= 1 if in_grand_coalition and coalition_dissent > 0; kpd_coalition_dissent += 1; kpd_relation -= 5; inflation -= 0.3; unemployed += 0.4; economic_growth -= 0.2;

We have reduced levels of social welfare spending. This means more poverty and suffering for the working class. The Communists and Social Democrats are criticizing us for our actions.


@increase_spending_pre_depression
view-if: unemployed <= 15
choose-if: budget > 0
subtitle: -1 Budget
