We have increased welfare spending. Our labor unions are pleased.

@increase_spending_post_depression
view-if: unemployed > 15
choose-if: budget > 0
on-arrival: budget -= 1; workers_z += 2*(1-dissent); unemployed_z += 2*(1-dissent); spd_relation += 5; kpd_relation += 5; coalition_dissent += 1 if welfare > 0; welfare_goal_completed += 1; inflation += 0.3
subtitle: The increased levels of unemployment necessitate more spending on aid to maintain the same benefits. -1 Budget

Increasing welfare spending is necessary in light of the rise in unemployment, so we are essentially treading water.

@spending_same_pre_depression
view-if: unemployed <= 15

We have kept welfare spending the same.


@spending_same_post_depression
view-if: unemployed > 15
on-arrival: workers_z -= 3; unemployed_z -= 3; welfare -= 1; right_labor_dissent += 4; left_labor_dissent += 4; kpd_coalition_dissent += 1; kpd_relation -= 8 if in_popular_front or in_left_front
subtitle: The increased levels of unemployment necessitate more spending on aid.

Increasing welfare spending is necessary in light of the rise in unemployment, so we have essentially cut welfare. The workers are justifiably displeased - we are sacrificing their livelihoods for the sake of fiscal orthodoxy.

[? if in_popular_front or in_left_front: The KPD is turning against us for our welfare policy. ?]
